      <scopecontent id="aspace_c093d1f1483a45e8dacc5329df5952f8">
         <head>Description of the Papers</head>
         <p>John L. De Forest acquired these papers while serving as Sholem Asch's secretary. The bulk of the collection consists of correspondence addressed to Asch, many letters carrying dictated drafts of his response on them. There are four typescripts of essays by Sholem Asch as well as five scripts for a Christmas pageant performed in Stamford, Connecticut, in 1943. Also present is De Forest's typescript memoir (ca. 1991) entitled "My Hours with Sholem Asch."</p>  
      </scopecontent>
